3. Better Security
4. Easier Maintenance
5. Loose Coupling
6. Better Extensibility
7. Improved Reusability
8. Supports Polymorphism

=========================================================
ABSTRACTION vs ENCAPSULATION
=========================================================

Encapsulation:
--------------
How data is protected.

Abstraction:
------------
What functionality is exposed.

Encapsulation:
Implementation level.

Abstraction:
Design level.

Encapsulation:
Data + Methods + Access Control.

Abstraction:
Hide implementation and expose only necessary behavior.

=========================================================
INTERVIEW TABLE
=========================================================

Feature              Encapsulation      Abstraction
---------------------------------------------------
Focus                Data Protection    Hide Complexity
Question             How?               What?
Achieved Using       Access Specifiers  Abstract Classes
Includes Data Hiding Yes                Partially
Level                Implementation     Design
Goal                 Security           Simplicity

